IS  - 6
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper compares monopsonistic and competitive search equilibria. While the competitive equilibrium is efficient, the monopsonistic equilibrium is not: there is too much search, and the employment rate is too low.
AB  - This paper compares monopsonistic and competitive search equilibria. While the competitive equilibrium is efficient, the monopsonistic equilibrium is not: there is too much search, and the employment rate is too low.
